 Let me not whine and whimper about things over which I have no control.
 Let me continue to see sin through God's eyes and acknowledge it as evil. And when I sin, let me repent, and confess with my mouth my 
wrongdoing, and receive the forgiveness of God.  
 And when this world closes in on me, let me remember Jesus' example-to slip away and find a quiet 
place to pray. It's the best response when I'm pushed beyond my limits. 
 I know that when I can't pray, You listen to my heart.  
 Continue to use me to do Your will.  
 Continue to bless me that I may be a blessing to others. 
 Keep me strong that I may help the weak. 
 Keep me uplifted that I may have words of encouragement for others. 
 I pray for those that are lost and can't find their way.  
 I pray for those that are misjudged and misunderstood. 
 I pray for those who don't know You intimately. 
 I pray for those that don't believe. But I thank you that I believe.  
